mailSender::addAttachment()

Description
    public void mailSender::addAttachment(string $location, string $name, string $encoding, string $type)
	Adds the contents of the parameters to the array, $this->attachment[].  See Notes for array elements.

Parameters
    location
		A string value containing location information.
    name
		A string value containing name information.
    encoding
		A string value containing a message's encoding information.
    type
		A string value containing type information.

Notes
    The contents of the function's parameters are added as such:
	$this->attachment[]	= array("location" => $location, "name" => $name, "encoding" => $encoding, "type" => $type);

See Also
    mailSender::addBCC()
    mailSender::addBody()
    mailSender::addCC()
    mailSender::addRecipient()
    mailSender::addReplyTo()
	mailSender::addSender()
	mailSender::addSubject()